item.title: Facts of week 42
item.description: I can remember what was taught in my Applied Linguistics class by the shirt my professor wore. My biggest secret is an unending fascination for the Momversation in which mommy bloggers discuss motherhood. Some people in my Dutch Language and Culture program are bad at spelling. All of them want to be writers. Times a day I realize I probably don’t want kids: 17. I’m terrified of failing University. During the day I’m scared, and when I’m not scared, I’m asleep.
